    1) add a 1 line description at the top
    2) use pkg group "adjoint" in some experiments
    3) use similar ordering of pkgs in packages.conf:
      a) eesupp pkgs (e.g., exch2, coupler-pkgs)
      b) dyn-core pkgs (e.g., gfd pkgs, mom pkgs, cd_code, gad, obcs ...)
      c) SGS-scheme (+ atm physics) pkgs (filters, gmredi, vert.mixing ...)
      d) forcing pkgs (e.g., rbcs, exf, cal, ebm, cheapaml)
      e) other component pkgs (e.g., ice, land, ptracers, biogeo, flt)
      f) diagnostics pkgs (e.g., sbo, profiles, layers, diagnostics, timeave)
      g) I/O pkgs, e.g., mnc (+ mypackage at the end)
      -- blank line --
      h) adjoint related pkgs (e.g., autodiff, ctrl, cost ...)
    4) remove unused pkgs: kpp, sbo, timeave ; this results in reduced number of
       TAF recomputation warning for AD exp: bottom_ctrl_5x5 & global_ocean_ebm;
